defaultRichard Gordondefault: I think it is necessary. Let us consider, for example, the first section of the Constitutional Reform Act, or rather let us consider the Lord Chancellor’s oath, which is to respect the rule of law. That is an oath, it is a promise. What does the rule of law mean? If you don’t have a rule for what the rule of law means, some kind of broad yardstick for what it means, you are going to get the judges possibly being able to hold, in some shape, size or 
defaultform, that
